    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but if the original meaning is so hard to pin down because language changes, doesn't that just give judges a lot of room to pick and choose history that fits their own views? how do you tell the difference between someone actually doing originalist research and someone just using history to justify a decision they already made?",
