      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The perceived ambiguity is a weakness that critics exploit, but rigorous originalism demands a disciplined, multi-faceted historical inquiry into public understanding, not just the private thoughts of the framers. The difference between genuine scholarship and judicial maneuvering lies in the methodological commitment to objective historical evidence, which must be applied consistently across all cases. If a judge cherry-picks history, they are abandoning the originalist premise and simply engaging in judicial activism.",
